etch data when a component mounts?\\n3. How does React’s virtual DOM work? Why is it beneficial?\\n4. Describe how you would manage state in a large React application. Compare Context API versus Redux.\\n5. What are React keys and why are they important when rendering lists?\\n\\nRESTful APIs:\\n1. What principles define a RESTful API? Give examples of resource-based URLs.\\n2. Explain the differences between GET, POST, PUT, PATCH, and DELETE HTTP methods.\\n3. How would you implement pagination in a REST API? Describe both client and server considerations.\\n4. What are CORS and CSRF? How do you handle them in a web application?\\n5. Describe how you would secure REST endpoints. What authentication and authorization strategies would you use?\\n\\nYears of Experience (5+ years required):\\n1. Describe a challenging project you led using JavaScript/React. What was your role and outcome?\\n2. How have you mentored junior developers? Provide an example of knowledge transfer.\\n3. Discuss a time you optimized application performance. What tools did you use and what was the result?\\n4. Have you contributed to open-source projects or technical communities? Describe your involvement.\\n5. How do you stay current with evolving JavaScript and frontend technologies?\\n\\nQualifications (Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science or equivalent):\\n1. How did your academic background prepare you for front-end engineering?\\n2. Describe a significant academic project related to web development. What technologies did you use?\\n3. Have you completed any certifications or coursework beyond your degree? How have they impacted your work?\\n4. How do you apply theoretical knowledge (e.g., algorithms, data structures) in day-to-day programming?\\n5. Can you explain a complex computer science concept (e.g., event-driven architecture) to a non-technical stakeholder?\"}"}
